------------------------------\n\n\n\nWe do not share personal information with companies, organizations and\n\nindividuals outside of Google unless one of the following circumstances\n\napply:\n\n\n\n    - With your consent\n\n    - With domain administrators\n\n    <https://support.google.com/a?p=privpol_admin&hl=en>\n\n    - For external processing based on our instructions and in compliance\n\n    with our Privacy Policy\n\n    - For legal reasons\n\n\n\nYou can find more details regarding the information we share at\n\nhttps://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en&gl=KR#infosharing\n\n\n\n*Personal Information Processing Delegation*\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\nWe provide personal information to our affiliates\n\n<https://policies.google.com/privacy/key-terms?hl=en&gl=KR#toc-terms-affiliates>\n\nor other trusted businesses or persons to process it for us, based on our\n\ninstructions and in compliance with our Privacy Policy and any other\n\nappropriate confidentiality and security measures.\n\n\n\nIn particular, in order to provide our users located in Korea with our\n\nservices more smoothly and expeditiously, we have entered into a\n\ncontractual relationship with the following entities listed here:\n\nhttps://policies.google.com/privacy/additional?hl=ko\n\n<https://policies.google.com/privacy/additional?hl=en&gl=KR>\n\n\n\n*Privacy Controls*\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\nYou have choices regarding the information we collect and how it\'s used.\n\nLearn more about it here:\n\nhttps://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en&gl=KR#infochoices.\n\n\n\nYou can also visit the Privacy Checkup\n\n<https://myaccount.google.com/privacycheckup?utm_source=pp&hl=en>, which\n\nprovides an opportunity to review and adjust important privacy settings.\n\n\n\n*Ways to review & update your information*\n\n\n\n*My Activity*\n\n\n\nMy Activity allows you to review and control data that\'s created when you\n\nuse Google services, like searches you\'ve done or your visits to Google\n\nPlay. You can browse by date and by topic, and delete part or all of your\n\nactivity.\n\n\n\nGo to My Activity\n\n<https://myactivity.google.com/myactivity?utm_source=pp&hl=en>.\n\n\n\n*Google Dashboard*\n\n\n\nGoogle Dashboard allows you to manage information associated with specific\n\nproducts.\n\n\n\nGo to Dashboard <https://myaccount.google.com/dashboard?utm_source=pp&hl=en>\n\n.\n\n\n\n*Your Personal Information*\n\n\n\nManage your contact information, such as your name, email, and phone number.\n\n\n\nGo to Personal Info\n\n<https://myaccount.google.com/privacy?utm_source=pp&hl=en#personalinfo>.\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\n*If you use the Google Payments service provided by Google Payment Korea\n\nLLC, the Google Payments Privacy Notice below also provides details on how\n\nyour personal information is processed in that service.*\n\n\n\nGoogle Payments Privacy Notice:\n\nhttps://payments.google.com/payments/apis-secure/get_legal_document?ldo=0&ldt=privacynotice&ldl=ko\n\n\n\nYour purchases, credit history, and/or transaction information is available\n\nto you via a number of secure online tools we provide to all users to\n\naccess data. Sign in to your Google Account <https://myaccount.google.com/>\n\nto get an overview of the ways you use Google\'s services and access that\n\ndata.\n\n\n\nYou can also export your transaction history with Google Takeout:\n\n\n\n    1. Go to takeout.google.com.\n\n    2. Once the Google Takeout page opens, click *Deselect all*.\n\n    3. Select *Google Pay*.\n\n    4. At the bottom, click *Next step*.\n\n    5. In the 2nd section, select the file type, frequency, and destination.\n\n    6. Click *Create export*.\n\n\n\nFor more information, please visit the How to download your Google data\n\n<https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/3024190> Help Center article.\n\n------------------------------\n\n\n\n*If you use Google Cloud service provided by Google, the Google Cloud\n\nPrivacy Notice below also provides details on how your personal information\n\nis processed in that service.*\n\n\n\nGoogle Cloud Privacy Notice:\n\nhttps://cloud.google.com/terms/cloud-privacy-notice\n\nņØ┤ ņØ┤ļ®öņØ╝ņØĆ Google Ļ│äņĀĢ ļ░Å ņä£ļ╣äņŖżņØś ņżæņÜöĒĢ£ ļ│ĆĻ▓Įņé¼ĒĢŁņØä ņĢīļĀżļō£ļ”¼ĻĖ░ ņ£äĒĢ┤  \n\nļ░£ņåĪļÉśņŚłņŖĄļŗłļŗż.\n\n┬® 2023 Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA\n\n\n============================================================\n============================================================\nID: 1850b66346eccd76\nĻĄ¼ļČä: ņłśņŗĀ\nņĀ£ļ¬®: [ĻĄ¼ĻĖĆ] Ļ░£ņØĖņĀĢļ│┤ ņØ┤ņÜ®ļé┤ņŚŁ ĒåĄņ¦Ć\n######################\nOutput:', 'role': 'user'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '("entity"<|>GOOGLE<|>ORGANIZATION<|>Google is a multinational technology company that specializes in Internet-related services and products, including search engines, online advertising technologies, cloud computing, software, and hardware.)\n##\n("entity"<|>GOOGLE PAYMENT KOREA LLC<|>ORGANIZATION<|>Google Payment Korea LLC is a subsidiary of Google that provides payment services in Korea.)\n##\n("entity"<|>KOREA<|>GEO<|>Korea is a country where Google provides its services and has specific privacy policies for its users.)\n##\n("entity"<|>MY ACTIVITY<|>EVENT<|>My Activity is a feature that allows users to review and control data created when using Google services.)\n##\n("entity"<|>GOOGLE DASHBOARD<|>EVENT<|>Google Dashboard is a tool that allows users to manage information associated with specific Google products.)\n##\n("entity"<|>PERSONAL INFO<|>EVENT<|>Personal Info is a feature that allows users to manage their contact information, such as name, email, and phone number.)\n##\n("relationship"<|>GOOGLE<|>GOOGLE PAYMENT KOREA LLC<|>Google Payment Korea LLC is a subsidiary of Google that provides payment services in Korea<|>7)\n##\n("relationship"<|>GOOGLE<|>KOREA<|>Google provides its services in Korea and has specific privacy policies for its users in the country<|>8)\n##\n("relati